---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy | SciCalcX Online Computational Suite" description="Review the SciCalcX Privacy Policy. Learn about local storage usage, cookies, and data collection.">
  <div class="w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6 sm:space-y-8 font-sans">
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <div class="text-center md:text-left space-y-1.5 border-b border-brand-border/60 pb-4">
      <div class="text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-blue-neon">
        Legal & Compliance
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-brand-text">
        Privacy Policy<span class="text-brand-blue">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xs text-brand-text-muted">
        Effective Date: June 11, 2026. Learn how we respect your computational privacy.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Privacy details -->
    <div class="border border-brand-border bg-brand-gray-dark/40 rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8 space-y-6 shadow-xl backdrop-blur-sm leading-relaxed text-sm text-brand-text-muted">
      
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          1. Data Collection & Privacy
        </h2>
        <p>
          At SciCalcX, we believe your mathematical computations are strictly your own business. We do not transmit, collect, or store any of the formulas, numbers, matrices, or code coordinates you calculate on our servers. All mathematical logic and calculations are performed directly within your local web browser engine.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          2. Local Storage Usage
        </h2>
        <p>
          We use browser `localStorage` features solely to enhance your user experience. This allows our calculator pages to persist configuration options between sessions, including:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1.5 text-xs">
          <li><strong>Theme Preferences:</strong> Dark mode and light mode configuration attributes.</li>
          <li><strong>Calculation History:</strong> A rolling log of your previous inputs and outputs (capped at 50 records) so you can reload prior calculations.</li>
          <li><strong>Memory Values:</strong> The numerical values saved via standard memory operations (M+, M-, MR).</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You can clear your local storage history at any time by clicking the [Clear All] calculation history button in the sidebar panel or clearing browser cookies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          3. Cookies & Analytics
        </h2>
        <p>
          SciCalcX does not deploy advertising trackers or behavioral profiling cookies. We may use minimal, privacy-first analytics to monitor page performance, traffic sources, and loading speeds to ensure the site runs efficiently.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          4. Contact Information
        </h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions regarding our operational guidelines or privacy practices, feel free to contact us via email at <a href="mailto:support@scicalcx.com" class="text-brand-blue-neon hover:underline">support@scicalcx.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
